SIMPLE: heritable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heritable
<hw>Her"it*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>h⟦eacute⟧ritable</ets>. See <er>Heritage</er>,
<er>Hereditable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being inherited
or of passing by inheritance; inheritable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of inheriting or receiving by
inheritance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This son shall be legitimate and <qex>heritable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Heritable rights</b></col> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>,
<cd>rights of the heir; rights to land or whatever may be intimately
connected with land; realty.</cd> <rj><au>Jacob (Law
Dict.).</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heritage</ent>⟦br⟧
